parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to unexpected loss of power, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The key does not go all the way back to the start position after the car is started
the engine stalls or has difficulty starting
the cooling fan fails to turn on
the radiator overheats
the fuel pump fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as the seat belt may not properly restrain the occupant.
symptoms: The seat belt cable breaks
the seat belt buckle fails to latch
the seat belt fails to retract
the seat belt unfastens while riding in the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, vehicle fires, and potentially life-threatening accidents.
symptoms: Engine overheating
coolant leaks
smoke or steam coming from the engine
sweet or burning smell from the vents
exhaust leaks
anti-freeze smoke coming through the heater vents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause hot water to spill into the passenger compartment, potentially leading to injuries, burns, or discomfort.
symptoms: Hot water spills into the passenger compartment
fog or steam appears on the windshield
the heating system malfunctions
the air conditioning system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield washer pump can reduce visibility while driving, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The windshield washer fluid does not spray
the windshield washer pump is noisy
the windshield washer pump is leaking
the windshield washer fluid is not dispensed.
